Day 4

1. Create Project
2. Create App
3. Create folder template under project4
4. views.py
    def demo(request):
	return render(request,'demo.html')


5. in settings.py
	INSTALLED_APPS add myapp1
	DIRS : [os.path.join('template')] # This helps Django to know where to look for html files


6. student.html. Also create functions student1, student2 and student3
7. create a new folder static and place an image file inside that
8. On top of the html file register static tag {% load static %}
9. <img src="{% static 'student.png' %}" alt="loading" height='200px' width="200px"><br><br>

10. Create index.html
11. Create function index in views.py
